         <p class="- topic/p ">One power block consists of:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Power module (maximum 2)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Controller box</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Power connection board</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Capacitor board</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Fan with fan monitor</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Power Block Structure</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">One power block consists
of one or two power modules (max. 40 kVA)<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Up to two power blocks can be paralleled (max. 80 kVA)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Each power block has its own controller (max. 2 controllers)<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Data collection, communication, load sharing and parallel behavior
is controlled by the master controller</p>
                        </li>
                     </ul>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Inverter self-test is run at every start-up</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">10 kVA, 30 kVA and 50 kVA are derated</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Odd number of power modules is allowed</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
